Section 3: "CODE PATTERNS" (Main Center)
- Left Column (Bad Code in Red Border):
  - Heading: "// BAD"
  - Code block:
    // Before: each component fetches its own data
// AccountHeader: getRecord (account fields)
// RiskBanner: getRecord (risk + signals)
// CasesPanel: getOpenCases (case list)
// AgentforcePanel: stale because re-renders
// independently, context always 1 cycle behind
- Right Column (Good Code in Green Border):
  - Heading: "// GOOD"
  - Code block:
    // store.js — Summer 26 native state
export const accountWorkspaceStore = createStore({
  state: { account: null, cases: [], signals: [] },
  actions: {
    async load(recordId) {
      const data = await loadWorkspace(recordId)
      this.state = data  // all components update once
    },
    invalidateAfterSave() { this.load(this.recordId) }
  }
})

Section 4: "DEVELOPER PROFILE & CHECKLIST" (Bottom Row)
- Left Side: A 3D Pixar-style cartoon avatar portrait of a dark-skinned South Asian male with a full thick black beard, shoulder-length wavy dark hair pulled up into a messy top bun, warm friendly smile showing teeth, wearing a grey crew-neck sweatshirt with the word "MAGNETIC" on it, set against a warm orange bokeh background. The avatar is labeled "Bennie Joseph | Salesforce Architect". Next to it is a quote bubble: "Architecting intuitive systems, engineering scalable solutions."
- Right Side: A checklist with points: "Define state shape upfront: account + cases + signals", "Load is called once in root component, not in each child", "Selectors compute derived state — never compute in template", "invalidateAfterSave() called after every Apex write succeeds", "Agentforce panel subscribes to store — always has fresh context".
- Footer: A thin bar with icons for "LWC Summer 26", "Native Store", "Agentforce 2.0 Panel", "UI API v64.0" and the text "CODE SMART. AUTOMATE FASTER. DELIVER EXCELLENCE."

